\hypertarget{the-node.js-platform}{%
\subsubsection{\texorpdfstring{ \textbf{1.2 The Node.js
Platform}}{ 1.2 The Node.js Platform}}\label{the-node.js-platform}}

When you build applications on a monolithic architecture, the entire
application needs to be deployed with every update. On the other hand,
microservices have no dependency on the type of framework, technique or
programming language being used to build them. Your ability to release
REST-ful APIs for communication and other services is the only requisite
for microservice architecture.

\textbf{Key benefits of Node.js}

\begin{itemize}
\item
  Single-threaded: With event looping, the server uses a non-blocking
  mechanism to respond.
\item
  Super-fast: Codes are executed quickly on the V8 JavaScript Engine
\item
  Event-driven: `Events of Node.js' is a notification system that
  enables the application server to capture the response of the previous
  API call.
\item
  Buffer-less: There is no buffering as data is simply released in
  chunks.
\item
  Asynchronous: The non-blocking, non-synchronous Node.js libraries move
  to the next API and do not await the return data of the previous API.
\item
  Highly-scalable: Servers can handle as many requests as coming their
  way
\item
  Licensed: The program is authorized under a software license.
\end{itemize}

